record.text:
No constraints (nothing clearly protected).
No override rules (no signal for when authority returns).
No handoff clarity (no shared definition of done).

With no middle, the work doesn’t move.
It hovers, then comes back.

Most delegation doesn’t fail because people don’t care.

It fails when the handoff sounds like:
“Just take care of it.”
“I’ll jump in if needed.”
“I’ll know when it’s done.”

That leaves the system guessing.
